  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1130 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}, reserving juice in a large #bowl{}. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (quarter both limes for 4 servings). To bowl with pineapple juice, whisk in a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, juice from 1 lime wedge (2 wedges for 4), half the lime zest, half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), and a couple large pinches of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @sirloin steak{10%ounce} to bowl with marinade and turn to coat. Marinate at least ~{15%minutes}, turning steak periodically.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Core, deseed, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and thinly sliced). In a small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and remaining lime zest (to taste). Season with salt. Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pineapple and cook, stirring occasionally, until beginning to char, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and roughly chop. Wipe out pan.

Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade. Pat meat dry with #paper towels{}, then season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for pineapple over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat and transfer to a cutting board to rest. Wipe out pan, then heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in it over medium-high heat. Add onion, poblano, and remaining Southwest spice. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}. Slice steak against the grain into very thin strips. Divide among warm tortillas and top with veggies, pineapple, and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> These carne-loaded tacos are hearty, filling, and most of all—absolutely delicious! Tender bites of tropical-marinated steak are piled into warm tortillas along with charred veggies, tangy lime crema, and juicy pineapple. Taco' bout a weeknight win.